    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors not assessed are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The primary validation dataset (vintage 2025-02-21) predates the model revision date (2025-03-17) by approximately 24 days; however, the assessment team determined that the intervening mesh revision — a localised trailing-edge refinement in the volute region — was not material to the hemolysis QoI. Global torque coefficient changed by less than 0.3% and NIH predictions at the five operating points changed by less than 1.1% in sensitivity runs. On this basis, the team accepted the existing validation evidence without initiating a formal re-validation study against updated model outputs. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met at all operating points. Credibility assessment outcome: Accepted.",
